Twenty-five customary court judges who were approved by the Abia State Judicial Service Commission (ASJSC) have been sworn in by the President of the state Customary Court of Appeal (CCA), Justice Anyalewechi Onwuchekwa, at Umuahia, the state capital. The post Abia swears in 25 customary court judges appeared first on The Guardian Nigeria News – Nigeria and World News. Source: Guardian